          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Both approaches work depending on event complexity. Simple events (weddings, private parties, workshops) should use built-in forms - Mixo, Squarespace, and Webflow have form builders that collect registrations without friction. Keep visitors on your site, capture all data directly, control the experience. Complex events (multi-track conferences, festivals with multiple ticket types) benefit from external platforms like Eventbrite - specialized features, attendee management, check-in apps, handlingÂ§çÊùÇÁöÑ ticketing scenarios. However, always embed the external registration on your site using iframe or button rather than redirecting entirely. Hybrid approach works best: collect basic info on your site, then link to Eventbrite for payment and detailed registration. This captures early interest while leveraging specialized tools."
